Package org.beryx.streamplify.benchmark

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DelayedBenchmark
    This benchmark shows that in situations where the iterator's next() method is time consuming, the IteratorSpliterator created by Spliterators.spliterator(Iterator, long, int) is not adequate for parallel processing, and the LongIndexedSpliterator should be used instead.
    FibonacciBenchmark
    Performs parallel and sequential benchmarks on the Fibonacci class.
    IterSpliterPermutations
    This class is functionally equivalent to LongPermutations, but it doesn't use the LongIndexedSpliterator.
    JacobsthalBenchmark
    Performs parallel and sequential benchmarks on the Jacobsthal class.
    NQueensBenchmark
    Compares the performance of LongPermutations with that of IterSpliterPermutations, which is a functionally equivalent class, but uses the IteratorSpliterator created by Spliterators.spliterator(Iterator, long, int).
    ShufflerView
